We will do our absolute best to partner with you, the parents, to nurture and bring out each child’s potential and to create a solid foundation for future years of education.

Little Explorers Preschool and Kindergarten is a school designed to provide excellent Christian education. We are registered as a school with the state of Oregon. All of our staff members have years of educational experience, and are regularly trained in updated teaching methods. It is the goal of all of our staff to help develop the basic skills of children through exploration, imagination, and creativity in a safe, secure, and friendly environment.

New Hope Community Church is a non-denominational church that exists to help people grow in Faith, Hope, and Love, and introduce their neighbors to Jesus.

name: Stepping Stone Day School Center-Highland
details:
At Stepping Stone Day School in Gresham, Oregon we strive to provide safe, loving and nurturing childcare at all times. We believe that each child is unique, special and learns best when they are safe, engaged and interested in exciting activities.

Our age-specific programs and curriculum provide fun and educational opportunities that assist in developing the “whole child”: developmentally, socially, and intellectually all while maintaining a high level of respect for each child and their family. At Stepping Stone Day School you will feel confident that your child’s needs will always be respectfully met.

name: Camp Fire Columbia at Trillium Creek Primary
details: Camp Fire Columbia is a co-educational non-profit organization that creates learning opportunities for more than 10,000 Portland area youth each year. Since 1911, Camp Fire Columbia has been an innovative leader in youth development, instilling a sense of pride in the community and providing opportunities for youth to find their *spark*. Through year-around educational and recreational opportunities, Camp Fire fosters an environment where youth can grow and realize who they are and what kind of impact they want to make on the world. Our promise: engaged, confident, well-rounded youth today can build thriving communities tomorrow.

name: SouthLake Preschool
details: SouthLake Preschool is a place where your child will feel loved, valued, and safe. We strive to glorify Jesus in all that we do. In order to meet your family's needs, our school offers high-quality Preschool for 2-5 year olds. We also offer Before and After Care available from 7am-6pm.

name: New Day Preschool
details: New Day Preschool is a modified Montessori school located in Tualatin, Oregon. We offer preschool for ages 2 1/2- 5 years including private, full day Kindergarten. We also offer before-school care as well as after-school care (for ages 2 1/2- 10 years). Students attending Byrom Elementary are welcome to join our after-school care program, where we offer homework help and fun activities for all ages. A bus from Byrom Elementary to New Day Preschool is available. Please call or visit our website for more information about our school as well as pricing.

name: Kidz Academy
details: The mission of KIDZ ACADEMY is to provide quality early childhood care for the parents of Hillsboro. Our program is designed to meet the needs of all children including those with disabilities. Our main goal is to bring a home daycare setting to a large center that way the parents and their children feel they have a home away from home.

name: McMinnville Christian Academy
details: The Christian philosophy of education is unique in contrast to all other educational philosophies. Other philosophies of education are man-cenered. Christian education is centered in the person of  Jesus Christ as revealed in the Word of God. The Christian philosophy holds that God, as the Ultimate Truth, becomes real to each person–man, woman or child–when that person accepts Christ, the crucified, risen Lord, through faith (“I am the way, the truth and the life” John 14:6). In keeping with these convictions, the school administration builds, and the teacher teaches, a curriculum that is God-centered. The entire educational program is designed to bring glory and honor to God and to encourage reverence for all of God’s creation in the heart and mind of each student. The student does not learn reverence for God through the intellectual process alone, but through accepting Jesus Christ as personal Savior. The student will then be open to guidance of the Holy Spirit in the learning of  skill, knowledge, and values. Teaching does not become Christian because we teach biblical truths alone, but rather because these truths are exemplified and practiced in the curriculum, activities, and everyday lives of students and staff. True Christian education is discovering and applying truth, seeing God revealed in truth, and recognizing that God alone is the Creator and that we are made in the image of God. The Bible is very clear in the establishment of the family unit as the primary social structure (Deuteronomy 11:19, Deuteronomy 6:1-9, Ephesians 6:1-4). MCA views itself as an extension of home; therefore, we exist to help parents meet their God-given responsibility to train their children to know and serve God.

name: Holy Cross Catholic School Pre Kindergarten
details: We, Holy Cross Catholic School, take Jesus as our model, in order to serve our diverse parish, surrounding parishes, and our entire neighborhood. We open doors to a rigorous Catholic education for all children, prekindergarten through eighth grade. The school, in the light of Christ, nurtures, affirms, and challenges students in their pursuit of learning and the responsibilities of faith and citizenship.

name: Lifeworks Northwest/Children's Relief Nursery
details: Our commitment is to work with children in the first, most important years of life. Our mission is to keep children safe and families strong. Our vision is to end child abuse and neglect in our community.

name: Little Village Montessori
details:
OUR MISSION
Little Village Montessori utilizes the natural curiosity of children to teach math, reading and critical thinking skills. 

We take a whole-child approach to education. 

Our teachers work together to meet the intellectual, social, behavioral, and emotional needs of each and every child we serve.

name: Cedarwood Waldorf School
details:
Cedarwood School brings Waldorf education to life and strives to instill a love for learning. Our curriculum weaves together the arts, academics and movement, with a reverence for the developing child. We nurture our children’s spirituality, cultivate their ability to think imaginatively and inspire them to seek the truth.

Our curriculum covers a full spectrum of traditional academic subjects and integrates artistic activities into the academics. This allows students to engage in learning at the emotional level. Painting, music and story are integral parts of academic lessons so that art becomes a conduit of knowledge, not an optional add-on. Kinesthetic learning is also interwoven through movement and crafts. Cedarwood cultivates a love of, and respect for, nature and the rhythms of the seasons through seasonal celebrations and daily time outdoors.

Cedarwood School first opened in October 1997 with one teacher and four students. Now, with over 280 students and a full array of subject classes, we have a thriving program. This has been further enhanced and enabled by the recent completion of a newly renovated wing on our beautiful building. In addition to two new classrooms, this renovation has given us a community kitchen, a spacious faculty room, a gorgeous performance space, an art display hall, and a fantastic music room. We can now truly serve our full pre-kindergarten-through-Grade 8 program and better share the fruits of this education with the Cedarwood community.

name: Sunny Day Preschool
details: We are a Christian-principled, co-operative preschool, utilizing play, nature, and creativity to inspire young minds and prepare them for Kindergarten.

name: The International School
details:
The International School provides a warm, multicultural environment where children are fully immersed in Spanish, Japanese or Chinese from preschool through 5th grade. Its small classes and inquiry-based, International Baccalaureate curriculum enable children to acquire language and culture as they learn to pursue knowledge beyond the classroom and throughout life.

The International School is Portland's first International Baccalaureate elementary school. It was founded in 1990 and today educates over 480 students from age 3 through 5th grade.

name: Safari Sam's
details:
At Safari Sam’s, we’re serious about having fun, and we’re also serious about providing the best care your children will ever experience. 

Oregon State Certification includes:
    15:1 child:staff ratio
    Criminal Background Check on all teachers and staff
    First Aid and CPR Training
    15 hours of continuing education annually

name: A Family Place
details:
A Family Place helps reduce childhood abuse, neglect and foster placements in Yamhill County.  

We support at-risk families by offering free professional home visiting, parent education and specialized preschool for children ages 0 to 5 – the time research shows these programs to have the greatest long term impact on children’s development.

A Family Place combines community support and proven methods to invest in the future of Yamhill County’s children.
business hours: Monday through Thursday 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.

name: St James Preschool/School
details:
Timeless Vision Statement:
Guided by Catholic faith, St. James School is committed to assisting students reach the fullness of Christian life by providing a complete educational experience developing their physical, moral, and intellectual talents.
Our Mission Statement:
The Mission of St. James Catholic School is to work in partnership with parents to provide a Christ-centered, safe, and creative environment for learning. Students grow toward their spiritual, intellectual, emotional and physical potential.

name: Head Start - (NH) Friendly House
details: Friendly House Preschool is based on the belief that children need an individualized early childhood education program that focuses on each child’s social, emotional, cognitive, and physical development. We provide an environment for children’s growing social interactions, and promote cooperation, and problem solving skills, as well as kindergarten readiness.

name: ChildRoots NW LLC
details:
We see all children as authentic, powerful individuals.

We recognize that a strong, consistent, and healthy bond between primary care providers and children is a necessary foundation for healthy growth, learning, and development.

Our teachers are co-learners. They are trained to observe, research, and support your child’s natural exploration of the world. Through open dialogue and side–by–side experimentation, teachers and children develop “curriculum” together.

All of our staff model the behaviors we hope to foster in children: curiosity, engaged scientific investigation, and treating ourselves and each other with respect, wonder, and awe.

We value community, not only in the classroom, but in our neighborhood and among the extended families whose children attend our Center. Enrolled families are encouraged to attend a variety of annual community events that we host throughout the year.

We are committed to business practices and early childhood education based on principles of environmental sustainability and social responsibility.

name: ChildRoots Center for Young Children
details:
We see all children as authentic, powerful individuals.

We recognize that a strong, consistent, and healthy bond between primary care providers and children is a necessary foundation for healthy growth, learning, and development.

All of our staff model the behaviors we hope to foster in children: curiosity, engaged scientific investigation, and treating ourselves and each other with respect, wonder, and awe.

We are committed to business practices and early childhood education based on principles of environmental sustainability and social responsibility.

name: Peninsula Children's Learning Center - Sabin
details:
Founded in 1970 as St. Johns Day Care, Peninsula started out in a church basement with seven children. The founders of Peninsula Children’s Learning Center were so committed to their goal of providing quality, affordable child care that a sliding-scale fee system was in place within a year of the Center’s opening – ensuring that families of all income levels would have access to quality child care and education.

Our mission to provide high quality child care and education as well as family support services to all members of our community demands a high commitment to fundraising and securing partnerships to support our sliding fee scholarship scale, additional financial aid, and to bridge the gap between Oregon Department of Human Services child care tuition reimbursement and our true cost of care. Each year Peninsula awards over $275,000 to families whose children would otherwise not be able to attend our program.

Today, we have the capacity to serve 219 children daily, and annually we average over 250 children served. Our community financed child care center is the heart of our Early Childhood Education Program . Our Before and After School Programs in Sabin and Boise Eliot Elementary Schools serve children ages 6 – 12.

Peninsula Children’s Learning Center is an independent nonprofit organization, overseen by a volunteer board of directors in conjunction with Executive Director Helen Kalk.

name: Christina's Preschool at Mcoy Village
address: 4542 NE Martin Luther King Jr Blvd
details: Our mission is providing families, children and staff a learning community in which all participants develop through a spiral dance of observation, inquiry, reflection and documentation. We create an intentional environment where each participant is respected as a responsible contributing member in our community. We see the participants as co-researchers, co-learners and collaborators in the building of our community.

name: Vermont Hills - Capitol Hill On-Site
details:
Vermont Hills Family Life Center (VHFLC) is a nonprofit organization that has provided quality childcare and preschool throughout the Portland metropolitan area (Banks, Beaverton, Hillsboro, Milwaukie, and Portland) since 1979. We currently service approximately 1,400 combined preschool and school age children in over 30 sites, some of which have NAEYC accreditation. VHFLC also offers 4 full-day summer camps for children entering 1st-8th grade.


    At VHFLC, we are dedicated to enriching the lives of children through an emotionally and physically secure environment that promotes self-esteem through positive role models and a well-defined curriculum. We respect each child's unique ability to experience fun, wonder and challenge, and prioritize the accommodation of every individual at his or her developmental stage.

    VHFLC not only supplies the family with nurturing childcare and preschool, but provides education, development and support through a variety of family services. We emphasize opportunities for staff growth, and place a high value on open communication, teamwork, and professionalism. Please don't hesitate to contact us with any questions.

name: Little Angels Academy
details: Little Angels Academy is a day care center for children ages 6 weeks to 3 years. With a low child to teacher ratio, each child receives special attention, which includes daily logging of the children’s routines, health, and behavior. Little Angels offers special rates and opportunities for single parents and parents who are in a lower income bracket, including training in all aspects of early childhood development. The Little Angels training program is offered in exchange for volunteer work from parents who can’t afford the cost.

name: MESP - Stephenson Elementary
details:
Stephenson Vision Statement
Stephenson School will provide a compassionate, caring environment where all students, staff and the community are challenged and motivated to achieve their personal, academic and creative best.

Stephenson Mission Statement
To prepare students to become responsible world citizens and life-long learners, Stephenson School is committed to becoming a professional learning community. We recognize art, music and second language as avenues to self expression and communication and as essential to the educational experience of all students.

Stephenson Elementary School is “at its best” when all individuals honor each student by name, value their individual contributions and recognize that all students have the ability to strive, shine and succeed. The Stephenson learning community is “at its best” with a continued collaborative partnership between school and a highly involved community.

name: Christ the King Parish School
details:
Christ the King Catholic School is rooted in teaching the loving message of Jesus to our school children.  The administration, faculty, and support staff work tirelessly on behalf of our students to be positive Christian role models and strive for each student to grow spiritually, academically, physically, morally, emotionally and socially.  The entire school staff works closely with parents, the primary educators of children, to ensure that each child has the opportunity to meet his/her potential.  Our school is blessed with a supportive parish community that works to promote the importance of our school’s ministry.  
 
Thank you for entrusting your children to the care of Christ the King Catholic School.  It is a ministry that our school community regards with compassion and sincerity.  May God bless the students, parents, and staff of Christ the King Catholic School and may the inspiration of Jesus shine in all that we do each day.

name: Ardenwald CARE
details:
Our Mission
Preparing graduates who are inspired and empowered to strengthen the quality of life in our local and global communities.

name: Our Redeemer Preschool and Kindergarten
details:
Our experienced and creative staff are dedicated to making your child's first school journey full of discovery and delight. Providing a solid foundation in faith formation, beginning school skills and positive character development are priorities.

Our Redeemer Preschool and Kindergarten offers a balanced program of academic learning and child-directed exploration and play.  Our goals are that children love to learn, love to come to school and are equipped to succeed at the next learning level.

The teachers at Our Redeemer are ready to partner with you as your child takes his/her first school steps.

name: Kids Incorportated Learning Center
details:
Our Center provides a warm, nurturing, secure setting where each child can develop to his/her own potential socially, emotionally, physically, and intellectually. The program is based on the following important beliefs: 
~ Process is more important than product. 
~ Children learn by doing. 
~ Each child’s unique creativity should be encouraged whenever possible. 
~ Each child and family have individual needs.

details: Our commitment is to work with children in the first, most important years of life. Our mission is to keep children safe and families strong. Our vision is to end child abuse and neglect in our community.

name: MECP - Lincoln Park Elementary
details: Welcome to Lincoln Park Elementary School. It is an honor to serve as the principal of this outstanding school. I look forward to our partnership in your child’s education. At Lincoln Park you will find fantastic teachers, a caring and knowledgeable staff, and a safe and fun learning environment for your children. You can help support this partnership at home by making sure your child arrives to school ready to learn and on time each day, help with homework, read with your child daily, and show an interest in what he/she is studying in school. Your encouragement will go a long way in helping your child feel successful at school.

name: L'Etoile French Immersion School
details: At L'Etoile French Immersion School we believe that children rise to the expectations that are set for them, and for this reason we set our expectations high.  Accredited by the French Ministry of Education, our approach to learning prepares children to be capable, confident students who are empowered to achieve in both French and English.  Our nurturing teachers engender a lifelong passion for learning and instill a respect for cultural traditions around the world.

name: Manos Unidas Montessori
details: Manos Unidas Montessori strives to follow the curriculums as set forth by Dr. Maria Montessori and to provide childcare that is both nurturing and stimulating.  Students are given tools for independence, academic success, social success, as well as respect and appreciation for all living things.

name: Community Action Early Head Start/Head Start - Middlegrove
details:
Head Start and Early Head Start programs promote the school readiness of children from birth to age five from low-income families by enhancing their cognitive, social and emotional development. Head Start began in 1965 as a summer program for low-income children. Today Head Start and Early Head Start programs serve almost a million children nationwide.

Community Action Head Start and Early Head Start programs offer high-quality early childhood education to families with children between six weeks to five years of age, who live in our Washington County service area, and whose family income is within 130 percent of the current federal poverty guidelines. (Families with income less than 100 percent of the federal poverty level are prioritized.)

In addition to education, Head Start and Early Head Start programs provide comprehensive services to enrolled children and their families. These include health, nutrition, social and other services determined to be necessary by family needs assessments. We welcome children with special needs and children who are learning English. Head Start services are designed to be responsive to each child and family's ethnic, cultural and linguistic heritage.

Stepping Stones Early Learning Center

Stepping Stones Early Learning Center’s mission is to prepare children academically, socially, physically, and emotionally for future educational and life experiences. At Stepping Stones children will become independent, successful and eager to learn how to creatively solve problems and express their ideas and feelings.
    Dedication: Our teachers encourage your child’s natural curiosity for exploring and learning new things while integrating structured educational activities.
    Child Centered: We recognize children are individuals and unique in their interests and learning styles. We have the ability to tailor our hands-on interactive lessons to suit the needs of each class and child.
    High Expectations: We continually evaluate and adapt our curriculum, enrichment classes, and teacher training, based on the latest research in early childhood education.

name: Little Lighthouse Preschool
details:
We offer a structured program within a caring, loving and nurturing atmosphere. To help with this we use the Frog Street Curriculum in all of our classes.  We allow children to grow, to experience new things and to feel secure and capable in God's world.  

Our goals for the children are:

*to develop language and communication

*pre-math and pre-reading skills

*encourage creativity and decision making 

*develop fine and gross motor skills 

*socialize in group interactions

We founded our preschool on the premise that learning should be an exciting experience for our children.  

We believe parents and teachers are partners in children's care and education.  We have an open door policy, and you are welcome all of the time!  ​

name: Kidco Early Head Start - Sweet Home Program
details: Kidco Head Start/Early Head Start is a free infant/toddler and preschool program that serves families from Linn, Benton and Marion Counties. Enrollment is based on age, income and special need. The infant/toddler program serves pregnant mothers children to 36 months of age.  The preschool program serves children who turn three or four years old on or before September 1st.  Four year olds are given priority at most centers.

name: Willamette Infant Toddler Center/Little Wolverine Preschool
details:
Welcome to Bethel’s high-quality early childhood programs, located on the Willamette High School campus. The Willamette Infant Toddler Center (ITC) & Little Wolverines Preschool/Child Care Center believe child care can and should be an opportunity for education, with children learning their best through play, interactions and experiences.

    The ITC is open to infants ages 6 weeks -24 months and toddlers 24-36 months who are children of current Bethel School District employees and current Willamette students.
    The Little Wolverines program welcomes children from the public at-large who are ages 3-6 years old.

Children in the ITC and Little Wolverines have the opportunity to learn through a data-proven, play-oriented approach to early childhood education. Our staff values, honors and respects the diversity and developmental differences in all children. It is our desire to meet each child where they are in their life’s journey and to add rich and meaningful experiences during their time with us.

The professional educators in the ITC and Little Wolverines programs provide opportunities for affectionate, nurturing, stimulating, and age-appropriate activities. Through developmental screening, evaluations, daily observations, and parent/family input we build the foundation for developing individual and group activities for children. We believe that all children should be allowed to develop and grow at their own pace.

The ITC and Little Wolverines programs foster an environment where children can succeed and where parents and staff work together to provide the very best experiences for their children.

name: After the Bell Afterschool Program
details: Student supervision is offered after school and is available at O’Hara by After the Bell. This program was established in Eugene in 2007 and is certified and licensed through the Oregon Child Care Division. After the Bell has its own payment program and is not part of O’Hara’s billing. After the Bell program for O’Hara students takes place on the O’Hara campus and is solely for O’Hara students. Students must be picked up on time or they will be sent to our after school extended care, After the Bell, at the parent’s expense.

name: Playdate Child Care Center River Road
details:
PlayDates Child Care Center provides high quality licensed full time, part time, and hourly drop-in child care. We create emotional attachments with the children and their parents by delivering a safe, educational, fun, and high energy center.

A center where parents can feel confident to leave their children when they are at work, when they have errands to run, when school is out, for Duck football care or any other reason.

We only hire loving, well qualified staff members who are energetic and responsible. We are all committed to helping the families of Lane County.

They also receive free medical and dental care, have healthy meals and snacks, and enjoy playing indoors and outdoors in a safe setting. Head Start helps all children succeed. Services are offered to meet the special needs of children with disabilities.

Early Head Start services are available for pregnant women, infants and toddlers in selected communities.

Head Start and Early Head Start works with the family, offering a sense of belonging, support services, and a chance to be involved in activities to help the whole family.

We assess children’s skills and abilities three times a year and use the data to plan for individual children and to make program improvements to ensure children are ready for kindergarten.

We provide developmentally appropriate activities based upon child growth and development theories, recent research in child development, and the time-tested culture of childhood. We recognize that as we all learn and grow our thinking must be flexible and open to review, modification and change. We view parents as partners and we strive to support the family through involvement and educational opportunities at ABC Early Learning Academy.

name: Building Blocks Child Care Center Inc
details:
Building Blocks Child Care Center believes that children are unique individuals.  Our goal is to provide an experience, which meet the child’s physical, social-emotional, creative, and intellectual needs.  Our program provides exposure to all of these areas of development daily. 
 
Through hands on experience, children have the opportunity to explore their own individuality and creativity.  We have both individual and group activities so the child not only learns about their world, but what role their peers have in it as well.  Our staff provides a warm and nurturing environment where the child can feel safe and secure. 
 
We are not biased against an individual’s race or religion.  We strive to strengthen the child’s own cultural identity, and help them develop a respect for others who may be different.  We encourage parent involvement whenever possible, inviting the parents to visit throughout the day as often as they like.

name: Country Acre Child Care and Early Learning Center LLC
details: It is Country Acre Child Cares philosophy to provide a warm, welcoming environment where children can learn through play, thrive on experiences, and discover their inner-selves. Here at Country Acre we have a goal to help the children reach great achievements through exploration and play. It is important to us that children get the opportunity to explore their boundaries and learn new lessons every day. Children will get the opportunity to be creative and express some of what they’re learning through arts and crafts offered daily. While outside, kids get space to run, and nature to explore on the organic playground. It’s our belief that children need room to make their own choices, so most of their day spent at Country Acre will consist of children directing their own activities, while teachers lend a helping hand along the way. We also will strive to offer organic/non gmo food choices whenever possible and are looking forward to offering an early achievers program to all our children.

name: Columbia Crest Montessori
details:
Preschool is the first and the most significant step in the life of a young child. It is at this juncture that we come along to help this transition as smooth as possible. At Columbia Crest Montessori we are committed to provide a nourishing and enriching environment for young children. This is the place where young kids are equipped with all the tools they need to flourish in their elementary years - learn how to follow directions, interact with others, and work in a group or part of a team and relate to grownups who aren't their parents.

At Columbia Crest Montessori, teachers focus on the child as a person, not on the daily lesson plan. Teachers lead children to ask questions, think for themselves, explore, investigate, and discover. Our ultimate objective is to help students learn independently and retain the curiosity, creativity, and intelligence with which they are born.

details:
Gan Yalduti is an Israeli /Jewish Preschool located in Bellevue WA. 
licensed by the Department of Early Learning (DEL). 
​
Gan Yalduti is a playful place where teachers and parents work together to create a warm, inspiring and loving atmosphere for children. We believe that preschool prepares children for what is to come, in all areas of their lives-both academic and social. We pledge to promote self-confidence, fearlessness, curiosity and dignity and to recognize these traits as important in everyone. 

​Our philosophy continues to evolve. There are, however, several concepts that are basic to our program:

To help children develop feelings of self-worth, independence and self-confidence. 
To expose children to many kinds of learning experiences. 
To treat children as unique individuals. 

To develop a sense of Jewish identity.

To encourage positive social awareness and interaction. 
To awaken an awareness of nature through indoor and outdoor experiences. 
​To help children learn to make a positive contribution to their own family and community.

details:
Every program, choice, and educational practice must meet our pinnacle questioning proclamations:

“Is it good for kids? Is it safe for kids?”

name: JOURNEY SCHOOL
details:
Our philosophy is based in our belief that children are competent individuals who can construct their own meaning of their experiences. The teacher’s role is not to provide all the correct answers. Rather, the teacher provides the occasion for discovery and learning. Our approach is hands-on and multisensory. We recognize that children have a natural curiosity and a predisposition to enjoy the unexpected. Children engage in active exploration and investigation to make sense of their world. We strive to fuel children’s investigative impulses and encourage discovery, promote questioning and challenging of ideas, and formulate connections of experience.

We respect children’s multiple ways of demonstrating their intelligence. Children are encouraged to develop their individual strengths and each child’s unique contribution to their community is appreciated. Strengths are celebrated and valued while opportunities are created to provide exposure to, and enhancement of, other talents and skills. Children will be given the opportunity to express themselves through music, painting, drama, song, movement, and play.

A Journey School’s program draws from several models of child development including the Reggio Emilia model to create an inclusive, child-led, emergent program steeped in the belief that children are strong, capable, creative thinkers who can explore their ideas in myriad ways. Components which will be incorporated into our program include:

    Classrooms that are beautiful, inspirational spaces
    Children, family, teachers, parents and community as interactive and collaborative
    An awareness and appreciation of the natural world in which the environment is viewed as co-teacher
    Opportunities for artistic expression in a variety of media
    Documentation of children’s activities and exploration through a portfolio system

At Sundance Preschool & Kindergarten, children express themselves through creativity and when given the freedom in the appropriate environment, they will discover a lifelong love of learning.
 
At Sundance we pride ourselves on providing an environment that allows children to discover the world around them. Individual learning styles are respected and diversity is celebrated. By providing a rich, nourishing environment with a variety of stimulating activities, children will see that learning is fun. When children reach a more structured environment in kindergarten, they will have the skills they need in order to be successful.

 Sundance students have strong self-esteem, a love of learning and the ability to make choices and solve problems by working together. Contact us today to set up a tour.

name: Sunshine & Rainbows Child Development Center
details:
Sunshine and Rainbows Child Development Center: provides a childcare setting that surpasses most daycares by providing a full service agency for parents and families.   Staff are qualified to provide services in Behavior Management, Developmental Therapy, Early Childhood and are trained to provide a preschool like environment all day long.  Childcare is something needed in every community and in this small community Concerned Citizens operates the only Center based program in the city.  Referrals for specialized childcare situations come to the Center from the Department of Social and Health, Developmental Disabilities, Child Protective Services, Doctors and Hospitals from as far away as Seattle.

Families are trying to juggle the challenges of working , shuffling families needs and after school activities. Sunshine and Rainbows strives to provide a well rounded curriculum that addresses all the needs of the child and family.
  
The brain is the part of the body that allows us to feel joy or despair, to respond to others in a loving or angry way or simply to react.  These capacities don’t just magically appear - they result from the interplay between a child’s heredity and the experiences he or she has during childhood.  With the changing needs of families we try to provide the support parents and children need to be successful.  Allowing ongoing opportunities for the brain to grow, children to learn and meeting all of the needs of the children and families.

details:
The Gan Garrett Jewish Preschool was opened in Vancouver, Washington to serve the needs of the growing Jewish popluation. The Gan, is Hebrew for "garden". We have created an emotionally-safe learning environment where our children feel empowered to explore ideas, skills and an understanding of self; where they can blossom, flourish and grow to make the world around them a more beautiful place. Our mission is shaped by:

•Jewish values

•The Reggio Emilia Educational Approach

•An appreciation and respect for the child’s natural stages of development

•The belief that children build knowledge through personal experiences

•The recognition that the years of early childhood possess within them the capacity for life-long habits, behaviors and attitudes

•The belief that each child possesses a unique inner voice that needs to be heard and encouraged by both the child and by those around him.

We work collaboratively - our children, their families, and our teachers - towards meeting this mission. For preschoolers, ages 2 - 5. Call us to talk about making this the place where your child will grow, thrive, learn and love.

name: Two Rivers
details: Two Rivers School (TRS) is an alternative learning program of choice that emphasizes goal setting and personal responsibility for students in grades 6-12 who prefer a smaller school environment as they work toward a high school diploma. It began as a part-time evening program in 1987 and expanded to its current location in 1997. The school now serves approximately 110 high school students and 13 students in grades 6-8. Two Rivers provides onsite childcare for teen parents, plus access to Running Start, the Washington Network for Innovative Careers (WaNIC), and accredited online courses through the Snoqualmie Valley Virtual Academy (SVVA). Two Rivers School uses a non-graded, standards-based evaluation system where students work toward the 22 credits the district requires to graduate.

name: Worldkids Academy LLC
details:
At WorldKids Montessori School children, teachers and staff from all over the world come together to share their cultures and gain a sense of global awareness. We believe in creating a warm, nurturing environment where children feel secure and can gain confidence in their own abilities.

The WorldKids Montessori curriculum introduces our young students to culture through music, dance, food, language and dress, children expand their knowledge and understanding of the world.

Our curriculum introduces children to an excellent preschool curriculum that prepares them for the upcoming school years and immerses all students into Mandarin Chinese & Spanish! New cultures and traditions are explored monthly!

WorldKids students are learning new things every day by having fun and exploring the world by using their senses! Our young World citizens are developing their social, emotional, physical and cognitive foundations they need to succeed in their elementary school years- and throughout their lives!

At WorldKids-School we strongly believe in the approach of teaching in an "Immersion" learning environment! Students are immersed into Mandarin and Spanish! Enrolling your child in an immersion preschool or daycares can be more advantageous to your child's foreign language development than a program that offers a foreign language as a subject.

Children in total immersion programs work toward total fluency in the foreign language. They are more likely to "think" and function naturally in the language. "Normally, they are able to achieve an extremely high level of overall competency.
Full immersion is less confusing than a translation-based curriculum, which is more appropriate for the adult learner. In addition, in a full foreign language immersion program, children have an opportunity to pro-actively use and rehearse foreign language in a challenging, intimate, emotionally supportive environment that stimulates all their senses.

The​ WorldKids​ culture is devoted to helping each child grow toward independence by building confidence, competence, self-esteem and respect for others. More than an approach to education, ​we use a ​Montessori approach to life. ​
​

WorldKids ​classrooms ​follow the Montessori ​multi-age mix ​class-room philosophy and encourage children to learn from each other and take on different roles while they grow within their group.

name: VOA Gold Bar - ECEA / PGold Bar Elementary School
WEE CARE DAY CARE DEVINE
details: We believe children learn best by interacting and exploring the world around them. Through their daily experiences in our care, we help them understand better the world in which they live. By our words, actions, and the activities we plan, we facilitate a desire and excitement for learning and growth. We nurture, encourage, and build the self-esteem of each child as they begin to develop the potential that each one has unique to him or her. It is our goal that each child will develop a positive self-image and a strong foundation of skills for future development and growth.

name: Bainbridge Island Child Care Centers/Kids Club
details: At Kids Club, we believe that in order for children to develop a lifelong love of learning, they must engage with their surroundings and have support interpreting their experiences. Our trained and capable staff focuses on creating multiple opportunities for growth and development. Our daily schedule includes a combination of exhilarating outdoor games and activities, guided reading and study time, creative art projects, foods from around the world to taste and enjoy, and healthy social interactions.

name: CAMP FIRE AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAM - ENGLISH CROSSING
details:
The After School Program is held at English Crossing Elementary every day after school: 3pm-6pm. If you go to Cougar Creek, you will take a bus over to join us. If you’re coming from Lakewood Elementary, we will meet you and walk you down.

Each day after school you will get a delicious, nutritious snack, play outside, tackle your homework or do some reading, and participate in various activities. Our caring staff lead activities that focus on learning to make healthy lifestyle choices, developing friendships, and working together.

When you don’t have school, you will get to come to Camp Fire’s Camp Killoqua! This includes half days, school days off, teacher in-service days, and spring break! At camp you will get to explore, go boating, play camp games, sit around camp fires, and sing camp songs. It’s a great taste of summer camp all wrapped into one fantastic day! All of these days at camp are included in your After School Program registration.

name: Kids Co At West Mercer
details: Kids Co. on Mercer Island is located on the forested, park-like grounds of three Mercer Island elementary schools: Lakeridge, Island Park, and West Mercer. Kids Co. offers three programs at its Mercer Island centers: Before-school and after-school care and summer day camp.

name: FINCH EXPRESS
details:
The Finch PTO (Parent-Teacher Organization) has played an important role over the years for Finch students, teachers, and parents. It is described as having been a positive influence on the entire school and surrounding community, an excellent organization, and responsible for fostering many good friendships among parents and teachers.

 
Edith Rasmusson, a parent, recalls, "All working together to raise money to buy stage curtains and other extras to complete the 1946 building." This organization also sponsored a "Mothersingers" group in the 1940s and 1950s, which numbered between 40 and 50 members. All were mothers of Finch students and enjoyed performing around Spokane, including the Spokane Music Festival.
 
During the 1970s and 1980s, the PTO almost died from lack of support from a charging society. However, in recent years, there has been a new effort to revitalize the or organization. Once again, parents unite in a variety of projects to support the students of Finch. Students are especially fond of wearing PTO-designed sweatshirts, T-shirts, hats, and sweatpants in the school color of red with the school mascot, the mustang, outlined in white.
 
The time that our Finch families contribute to our school is invaluable! If you are interested in volunteering at an event for in the classroom please see our Volunteer Opportunties page for more information.

name: Redmond Ridge After School Program LLC
details:
Trinity Martial Arts is locally owned and operated by Chris Aprecio and his wife, Tiffany Aprecio. For over 18 years, they have taught self-defense and martial arts to thousands of residents throughout Washington including Sammamish Plateau and Overlake at True Martial Arts, Lake Stevens at Taigon Tae Kwon, in Arlington where Trinity Martial Arts opened in 2009 and moved to Redmond in 2013. Kyo Bum Nim Aprecio’s passion for martial arts began at age 5 and by 15 his life’s mission was to influence others through his teaching. Raised on the Eastside, the Aprecio’s enjoy being part of this great community.

Trinity Martial Arts is a family oriented martial arts school teaching Tae Kwon Do and Arnis, a Filipino Stick Fighting Art. The curriculum is designed to be progressive, both physically and mentally. The improvements anticipated for all student are to become physically better at martial arts while internally strengthening your mind and character. The Dojang (school) creates a safe atmosphere for students challenge themselves in areas they typically avoid. We want our students to approach everything they do in the Black Belt Way, with 100% effort, a positive attitude, and indomitable spirit.

name: SWCCC BURTON SCHOOL AGE
details: In 1989, Clark County's business, education and civic leaders joined Educational Service District 112 to take an extraordinary step: they launched the first of what has now become the largest community-run child care system in the United States. Today, this effort is recognized as one of the "best and brightest" examples of local, state and federal government programs addressing one of today's toughest issues: child care.

name: The Firs After School Adventure North
details:
ASA (After School Adventure) is a program of The Firs, serving Kindergarten through fifth grade students in the Bellingham and Meridian School Districts, during non-school hours; before school, after school, on early release days, teacher work days, some holidays and school vacations.

ASA offers programming from two sites. The main site provides care for most of the Bellingham School District and is located in a beautiful camp setting at The Firs, east of Bellingham on Cable Street (off of Lakeway Drive).  The second site serves Cordata Elementary and Irene Reither Elementary and is located at 400 Meadowbrook Ct., at Birchwood Presbyterian Church. Both sites offer unique facilities, giving students the maximum opportunity for fun and adventure!

Each year, the ASA program centers around a major theme, creating a backdrop of fun and adventure, making a child’s PLAY experiences new and exciting EVERY DAY!

name: YMCA - Birchwood/Whatcom
details: Girls on the Run encourages positive emotional, social, mental and physical development. Participants explore and discuss their own beliefs around experiences and challenges girls face at this age. Designed to allow every girl to recognize her inner strength, the Girls on the Run curriculum inspires girls to define their lives on their own terms. Throughout the season, the girls make new friends, build their inner confidence and celebrate all that makes them unique. Running is incorporated throughout the curriculum to inspire an appreciation of fitness and to build habits that lead to a lifetime of health. At the end of the season, the girls participate in a Girls on the Run 5k event. This celebratory, non-competitive event is the culminating experience of the curriculum. Completing the 5k gives the girls a tangible understanding of the confidence that comes through accomplishment as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals. Crossing the finish line is a defining moment when the girls realize that even the seemingly impossible IS possible.

name: Temple Beth El - Brotman Early Learning Center
details:
The renovation of our outdoor playground is well on its way. Your purchase of a brick paver, engraved with your name, your child’s name, in memory of...or in honor of...will benefit BELC, our religious school and the temple by creating a beautiful, functional play area for all our students. The pavers will be placed in the patio area between the corner of the building and the area with the large play structure.

Your inscription can be 1, 2, or 3 lines and up to 60 characters (please do not exceed the spaces available on the form). Paver size is approximately 2⅜ x 9 x 7 inches. Just complete and return this form by August 14 and help us pave the way.

name: EARLY BLOOMERS CHILDCARE
details: Our philosophy is that "play is a child's work". Children are competent, amazing learners that given the opportunity and support from parents and/or caregivers will develop and grow in their own unique way. Children deserve a childhood full of memories that are created by exploring, creating, and spontaneous discoveries. We can provide these experiences through a nuturing, well planned environment that encourages play, exploration, curiosity, and problem solving. Teachers act as facilitators to help children build upon their interests and knowledge by careful observation, meaningful interactions, and documentation. Children have the opportunity to work individually or collaboratively and may choose whether or not to participate in activities. There will be structured and unstructured periods throughout the day enabling children to play, learn, and grow at their own rate.

name: LITTLE DISCOVERY CHILDCARE
details:
We are an education centered childcare with excellent teachers to prepare your child/children for success in school. We believe that children given fun ways to learn now, will enjoy learning as they continue to grow. We do not focus only on the ABCs and 123s, we educate the children completely, including large motor skills, small motor skills and their creativity as well!

We are open from 5:30am until Midnight, Sunday through Saturday!! We serve two snacks, breakfast, lunch and dinner. We follow the USDA food program guidelines and serve the children healthy, balanced meals so that they can be even more successful! They also get at least two times every day to be outside and get fresh air and run around.

If you would like to know about our program, please give me a call. I would love to talk to you about our program! I am more than happy to answer any questions you may have. If you would like a tour, give me a call and we will set up a time for you to come in and check it out!

name: Assumption Catholic Preschool
details:
Assumption Catholic School enhances academic excellence in order to inspire students to reach their fullest potential. The parents are the primary educators of their children. Assumption Catholic School teachers work in partnership with parents to provide a caring atmosphere that prepares students for lives of service and respect for one another, their families, their school, their church, their community, and the global community.

Teachers, along with the school community, foster personal and social development within a secure environment that promotes self-discipline and peaceful process. Based on Catholic values, teachers and parents work together to offer learning that will develop skills necessary to make decisions regarding spiritual relationship with God, respect for life, fostering of diversity, and life-long health and sense of well-being.
